01:28.858 --> 01:31.100
-Where is he?
-He promised.

01:31.736 --> 01:33.230
You know his promises.

01:34.488 --> 01:37.262
-He's not gonna miss this, is he?
-He'll be here, sweetheart.

01:37.366 --> 01:40.599
But.... Well, that's okay, Joaquin,
put them all on the front of the float.

01:40.703 --> 01:42.017
Where's all the flags?

01:42.121 --> 01:43.200
Okay.

01:52.256 --> 01:55.115
-Jeff, for God's sake.
-l'm here. l'm ready.

01:55.219 --> 01:57.970
-l'm going. General Grant, right?
-Jeffrey. Jeff.

01:58.096 --> 01:59.785
-Get dressed!
-l'm getting dressed!

01:59.889 --> 02:01.621
-Go. Go!
-He had a beard, you know.

02:01.725 --> 02:04.512
-Jeffrey.
-Never mind! Never mind!

02:04.769 --> 02:06.846
l love it! lt's fabulous.

02:24.791 --> 02:27.272
-That looks like a blue ribbon.
-You say that every year.

02:27.376 --> 02:30.734
l know, we're right up front, between
Valley Realty and Darrell's Body Shop.

02:30.838 --> 02:31.918
l'm telling you.

02:36.761 --> 02:39.119
-You're not dressed!
-What do you mean, l'm not dressed?

02:39.223 --> 02:40.370
l'm dressed great.

02:40.474 --> 02:42.496
-This is a parade.
-And l'm ready to march.

02:42.600 --> 02:46.584
You look like you're ready to dance.
That outfit does not spell ''defence.''

02:46.689 --> 02:48.727
-What does it spell?
-''Barbara.''

03:08.878 --> 03:10.859
Do you still prefer McDonald's
for work experience?

03:10.963 --> 03:12.653
-Miguel!
-McDonald's for work experience.

03:12.757 --> 03:14.446
-l'm having second thoughts.
-Not now, Miguel.

03:14.550 --> 03:16.573
Ms McLaughlin,
l'm considering Long John Silver's.

03:16.678 --> 03:20.410
-l looked into the future and it may be fish.
-Miguel, after the parade.

03:20.515 --> 03:22.673
l'm busy with other people's futures
right now.

03:23.811 --> 03:25.749
Looks like you're doing fine, Sgt Leathers.

03:25.853 --> 03:27.918
l'll be over at the Army booth.
They always need help.

03:28.022 --> 03:30.380
And what are you gonna do after the parade,
Ms McLaughlin?

03:30.484 --> 03:33.354
-l think l'm gonna lie down.
-Alone?

03:33.695 --> 03:35.854
Stand by! Ten-hut!

03:51.255 --> 03:52.334
Hi.

04:06.688 --> 04:09.013
-Hey, Jeff. Jeff.
-Come on down here.

04:09.315 --> 04:11.380
-Hey, what are you guys doing?
-Air Force Academy.

04:11.484 --> 04:13.300
-They're setting up interviews.
-We gotta sign up.

04:13.404 --> 04:15.634
-Look here, cadet, how many fingers?
-What? What?

04:15.738 --> 04:19.014
''Four,'' the man said. Kee-rect!
Now, what's the colour of your white jacket?

04:19.118 --> 04:21.099
-You've lost it totally.
-The man said ''white.''

04:21.202 --> 04:22.266
''White'' is A-okay.

04:22.370 --> 04:24.394
-Certify him for night flying.
-You're in.

04:24.498 --> 04:26.563
-Congratulations, cadet.
-Sign right here.

04:26.667 --> 04:29.336
Give me it. ''Applicant,'' that's me.

04:31.255 --> 04:32.334
All right.

05:27.438 --> 05:30.225
What are you doing here?
You shouldn't be here.

05:33.444 --> 05:37.656
What do you want? Are you crazy? No!

06:13.152 --> 06:14.967
<i>It was the first summit handshake
in years....</i>

06:15.071 --> 06:18.903
-His tie comes from Paris.
-Certainly an improvement on Brezhnev.

06:19.367 --> 06:21.473
The suit is ltalian.

06:21.578 --> 06:24.532
Madam sends to Milan for her clothes.

06:25.707 --> 06:27.813
-What about my roof?
-Your what?

06:27.917 --> 06:28.997
My....

06:29.544 --> 06:31.169
His cover.

06:33.382 --> 06:36.631
San Diego County Agricultural Exchange.

06:37.637 --> 06:39.012
You know the area?

06:40.555 --> 06:41.634
lntimately.

06:42.641 --> 06:46.457
When you reach San Diego,
you have not only the FBl to deal with....

06:46.561 --> 06:50.545
Also the Navy lnvestigative Service,
the Defence lnvestigative Service...

06:50.650 --> 06:53.140
plus Customs and lmmigration officials.

06:53.485 --> 06:55.609
San Diego is very active.

06:56.155 --> 06:57.863
You do understand?

06:57.991 --> 07:03.032
Young man, l was crossing into the West
before you could spell Bolshevik.

07:04.871 --> 07:07.743
A canon is loose in San Diego.

07:07.876 --> 07:11.956
-You know him. He belongs to us.
-The Americans have coded him ''Scuba.''

07:12.922 --> 07:14.796
Their attempt to be amusing.

07:15.175 --> 07:20.002
You are to apprehend Scuba.
He has killed one of our best agents.

07:20.305 --> 07:24.718
-Scuba is an embarrassment to the premier.
-The premier prepares for the summit.

07:24.851 --> 07:28.919
-A sideshow.
-This lRS man was working for us.

07:29.023 --> 07:33.899
Scuba is blackmailing us. He will keep
killing our agents until we give him money.

07:34.195 --> 07:38.774
Return Scuba to Russia, alive.
That is your assignment.

07:39.534 --> 07:42.025
You have seen the dossier
on your backups?

07:42.203 --> 07:44.196
l prefer our man in Vancouver.

07:44.497 --> 07:47.498
-The operative word is discretion.
-No press.

07:47.875 --> 07:49.702
No publicity.

07:50.003 --> 07:51.413
No news at all.

07:51.671 --> 07:54.756
What we fear most is the American media.

07:55.758 --> 07:59.174
l remember when we used to fear the ClA.

07:59.888 --> 08:02.461
Everything changes, Karpov.

08:04.976 --> 08:08.926
<i>This Iatest series of taIks
between the two great superpowers.</i>

08:09.314 --> 08:11.022
Nothing changes.

08:11.149 --> 08:13.799
<i>The first historic meeting
between these two worId Ieaders...</i>

08:13.903 --> 08:15.645
<i>signaIs the beginning of a new chapter....</i>

08:55.655 --> 08:57.678
More applications, Roy.

08:57.782 --> 09:00.984
These didn't come up kosher, either.

09:01.702 --> 09:05.810
l say that we've got a run
on the Air Force Academy this year.

09:05.914 --> 09:07.991
That's one way to beat Army.

09:10.378 --> 09:13.235
Chief, you're drowning me in paper.

09:13.339 --> 09:18.085
Stats, Roy, stats.
The inspector's going to pay us a visit.

09:18.595 --> 09:21.631
Did you see the thing
about the lRS man at Caliente?

09:21.848 --> 09:23.390
What lRS man?

09:23.683 --> 09:26.803
The one they found behind the pari-mutuel
with his throat cut.

09:29.731 --> 09:32.671
What do you and Totten do in here
every morning at 6:00 a.m?

09:32.776 --> 09:34.716
Check the Hong Kong prices?

09:34.820 --> 09:36.091
l know a horse player.

09:36.196 --> 09:40.389
Forget about Scuba, Roy.
The man is a burnt-out double agent.

09:40.493 --> 09:44.558
Scuba has been turned so many times
he looks like an omelette.

09:44.663 --> 09:46.822
The man killed my partner.

09:48.500 --> 09:51.039
You don't know if he killed him or not.

10:01.305 --> 10:04.093
Jesus, Roy, that was 20 years ago.

10:05.435 --> 10:06.549
So what?

10:09.981 --> 10:13.480
l gotta go. l'm presenting
the hole-in-one trophy tonight.

10:16.071 --> 10:18.526
Hey. Hang in there, Roy.

10:31.254 --> 10:33.459
Okay, let's see this kid.

11:28.646 --> 11:30.638
What have we got here?

11:36.905 --> 11:39.762
l need a reading
on Richard and Elizabeth Grant.

11:39.866 --> 11:41.823
Fountain Grove, California. Son, Jeffrey.

11:44.287 --> 11:45.366
Yeah.

11:46.623 --> 11:48.366
lt doesn't track for me.

11:52.170 --> 11:54.127
Did these people die or what?

11:59.137 --> 12:01.367
-Go, Air Force!
-Yeah, go, Air Force.

12:01.471 --> 12:03.096
Will you sit down?

12:04.017 --> 12:06.685
-Turn the radio off.
-Hey, look at this guy.

12:09.062 --> 12:10.439
Jeffrey Grant.

12:13.066 --> 12:15.356
-All right.
-Go get them.

12:17.197 --> 12:18.302
Good luck, buddy.

12:18.406 --> 12:21.193
And remember,
''You live in fame or go down in flame.''

12:43.933 --> 12:45.592
Excuse me, Corporal.

13:10.919 --> 13:13.588
-What do you think?
-Sorry?

13:14.339 --> 13:15.749
Corporal Hogan.

13:16.424 --> 13:17.587
Oh, her.

13:17.968 --> 13:22.118
-Yeah, yeah, she was very nice.
-Yes, very nice.

13:22.222 --> 13:25.591
Sometimes l slip up
and call her Corporal Hogans.

13:27.562 --> 13:31.689
Roy Howe, Jeff, Air Force Reserve Liaison.
l'll be conducting your Academy interview.

13:32.734 --> 13:35.437
You got a wet palm there, son.
What's the matter? Nervous?

13:35.569 --> 13:37.550
-Yeah, l'm nervous.
-What are you nervous about?

13:37.654 --> 13:40.387
-l don't know. l want to pass.
-There's nothing to pass.

13:40.491 --> 13:43.576
This isn't a test. Relax. Be yourself.

13:44.370 --> 13:45.450
Okay.

13:50.418 --> 13:52.541
You are nervous, aren't you? Why?

13:53.587 --> 13:55.711
Because you told me to be myself.

13:55.924 --> 13:58.864
Whenever people tell me to be myself,
l don't know what to do.

13:58.969 --> 14:02.053
-How come?
-'Cause l don't know what myself is.

14:04.766 --> 14:06.924
-You like girls, Jim?
-Jeff.

14:07.102 --> 14:08.726
How do you feel about girls, Jeff?

14:09.521 --> 14:10.668
l love them.

14:10.772 --> 14:12.003
-You got a girl?
-You bet.

14:12.107 --> 14:13.379
-You have one girl?
-Yeah.

14:13.483 --> 14:14.630
No. Yeah.

14:14.735 --> 14:18.051
Yeah. l do have one girl,
and l like her a lot...

14:18.156 --> 14:20.112
but l love girls in general.

14:23.536 --> 14:25.077
You're doing fine.

14:25.954 --> 14:28.145
Why do you want to go
to the Air Force Academy, John?

14:28.249 --> 14:30.242
Jeff. Jeff, Jeff.

14:34.339 --> 14:36.877
l hear you. You hear me?

14:38.759 --> 14:41.168
l wanna fly. l wanna be a pilot.

14:41.554 --> 14:42.717
That's it?

14:43.139 --> 14:44.419
l love my country.

14:46.226 --> 14:47.289
That's all?

14:47.394 --> 14:49.333
Hey, what can l tell you? l gotta fly.

14:49.437 --> 14:52.355
-Why?
-l like to go fast.

14:53.859 --> 14:56.424
-l can see that.
-Only three tickets.

14:56.528 --> 14:57.592
ln a month?

14:57.696 --> 15:01.263
40 in a 35. l was on the freeway at 5:00 a.m.
Alone on the road--

15:01.367 --> 15:03.973
-You don't deserve the citation?
-No.

15:04.077 --> 15:06.236
Yeah, yeah, l do.

15:06.371 --> 15:08.660
l drive too fast. But l'm a good driver.

15:09.416 --> 15:11.456
Sorry. l'm working on it, sir.

15:12.587 --> 15:14.247
Work hard.

15:14.422 --> 15:16.710
Yes, sir. l will, sir.

15:20.512 --> 15:23.215
-Are you sucking up to me?
-Yes, sir.

15:24.099 --> 15:25.557
No, sir. l....

15:27.976 --> 15:30.729
What do your folks say
about your heavy foot?

15:31.273 --> 15:36.184
-Dad.... You know how fathers are.
-No, l don't know how fathers are.

15:36.820 --> 15:39.572
Well, he's not crazy about it.

15:39.823 --> 15:43.806
And neither is Mum. l can understand them.
They don't want me to get hurt.

15:43.910 --> 15:46.726
-What about your folks?
-What about them?

15:46.830 --> 15:49.437
There's nothing much to tell.

15:49.541 --> 15:52.543
My mum and dad,
they run a garden nursery, and....

15:54.004 --> 15:55.202
l love them.

16:00.177 --> 16:02.952
What do your folks think
about your going to the Academy?

16:03.056 --> 16:04.467
They don't know about it.

16:08.436 --> 16:10.643
l want to surprise them
with some good news.

16:14.859 --> 16:16.603
Did l say the wrong thing?

16:18.028 --> 16:20.520
No. Not at all, comrade.

16:27.038 --> 16:28.118
l'm sorry.

16:31.626 --> 16:33.085
l don't understand.

16:37.674 --> 16:39.418
-ls that all?
-For now.

16:43.305 --> 16:47.055
''Jeffrey N. Grant.''
What does the ''N'' stand for?

16:47.185 --> 16:48.810
-Nicholas.
-Nicholas.

16:49.770 --> 16:51.430
You of Greek extraction...

16:51.563 --> 16:53.420
or is your birthday near to Christmas?

16:53.525 --> 16:54.964
l don't know. l used to hate the name.

16:55.068 --> 16:58.551
Then l went through this period where
that's all l wanted to be called, ''Nick.''

16:58.655 --> 17:01.554
-l thought it was tough. Now l hate it again.
-We'll be talking again.

17:01.658 --> 17:03.900
-Great!
-About something else.

17:04.202 --> 17:06.906
-l thought l'd passed.
-For now.

17:07.289 --> 17:10.574
Blue skies, Jeff.
Happy landings and pack a tight chute.

17:14.172 --> 17:15.333
What was that?

17:15.714 --> 17:16.792
No good?

17:17.340 --> 17:19.963
l practised this morning. l thought l'd do it.
Now l blew it.

17:21.094 --> 17:22.423
lt wasn't too bad.

17:23.430 --> 17:25.424
Bye, Corporal Hogans.

17:27.809 --> 17:29.517
Good, Jeff, good.

19:43.450 --> 19:45.556
You must be tired, Comrade Karpov.

19:45.661 --> 19:47.684
No, just have nothing to say.

19:47.788 --> 19:50.458
l still do not understand
why they sent you here.

19:51.084 --> 19:52.791
To get the job done.

19:53.168 --> 19:55.735
l think we should go through
the list of your contacts again.

19:55.839 --> 19:58.653
-What for?
-To make sure you remember them all.

19:58.757 --> 20:02.092
-Even you could forget.
-l doubt it. l put them here.

20:03.555 --> 20:05.927
<i>Too bad about our IoveIy water-skier.</i>

20:06.183 --> 20:08.056
<i>She was a good agent.</i>

20:10.227 --> 20:13.099
Scuba made contact with you only once?

20:13.815 --> 20:15.755
As l told you, a brief message...

20:15.859 --> 20:19.442
''Pay $200,000
or l'll kill every agent on the list.''

20:20.405 --> 20:22.197
Only four more to go.

20:25.285 --> 20:27.776
l heard you gave him
the code name ''Scuba.''

20:28.456 --> 20:31.409
No, an FBl agent did.

20:32.167 --> 20:33.627
But why?

20:36.505 --> 20:37.999
He loves water.

20:38.757 --> 20:40.087
Like a shark.

20:40.677 --> 20:42.170
No, like a rat.

20:44.764 --> 20:47.469
Stop here, before we get to the border.

20:54.815 --> 20:57.142
We have organised a pickup
on the other side.

20:57.402 --> 20:59.644
l prefer public transportation.

21:00.488 --> 21:02.887
l guess that's okay,
but l don't have to tell you--

21:02.991 --> 21:04.189
No, you don't.

21:23.221 --> 21:28.381
<i>WeIcome aboard the San Diego troIIey,
bound for the Santa Fe Depot in centre city.</i>

21:28.810 --> 21:33.186
<i>We appreciate having you on board today
and hope you have a pIeasant trip.</i>

21:56.798 --> 21:58.077
You call a taxi?

22:09.810 --> 22:12.515
Are you the man
who wants to go to Fountain Grove?

22:23.365 --> 22:25.431
He crossed the border yesterday.

22:25.535 --> 22:28.157
Turned up in a coffee shop
in Fountain Grove.

22:28.413 --> 22:30.655
He didn't give up
on public transportation, did he?

22:32.125 --> 22:35.692
He was at the Union Station stakeout in D.C.
20 years ago when Scuba--

22:35.796 --> 22:38.631
Oh, yeah, right, right.
Look at that son of a bitch.

22:39.133 --> 22:41.042
He still looks real good.

22:41.760 --> 22:44.200
Why did you ask me in here
before everyone else?

22:44.304 --> 22:45.929
Because you're the best, Roy.

22:46.808 --> 22:49.539
l should be reporting to you,
instead of the other way around.

22:49.643 --> 22:51.959
-Don't stroke me, Jim.
-What do you want me to tell you?

22:52.063 --> 22:53.308
That l got Scuba.

22:53.856 --> 22:56.921
You know there's a case.
You can feel it inside, just like l do.

22:57.026 --> 22:59.883
Karpov is here to get Scuba.

22:59.987 --> 23:03.024
The Bureau is maintaining
a hands-off policy.

23:03.450 --> 23:06.556
Screw the Bureau. What is your policy, Jim?
You know l'm right.

23:06.660 --> 23:09.101
l don't give a damn
whether you're right or wrong, Roy.

23:09.206 --> 23:11.395
l just wanna see you get on with your life.

23:11.500 --> 23:14.869
Get it resolved. You owe it to yourself.

23:15.629 --> 23:17.088
So l got Scuba?

23:18.465 --> 23:21.864
Yeah, you got Scuba. He's all yours.

23:21.969 --> 23:25.801
But you're on your own.
lt is strictly unofficial.

23:26.056 --> 23:28.464
No one but me knows about it.

23:29.184 --> 23:30.382
Understand?

23:33.063 --> 23:34.261
Thanks, Jim.

23:38.485 --> 23:41.059
Don't forget your Air Force applications.

24:51.103 --> 24:56.310
So they spotted him
in a coffee shop in Fountain Grove.

24:56.650 --> 24:59.022
Fountain Grove? Wait a minute.

26:01.426 --> 26:04.241
Well, what's the big deal?
l'm just applying for traffic school.

26:04.345 --> 26:07.015
-Down the hall, Grant. Room 1 .
-Please.

26:07.140 --> 26:11.054
All l want is Saturday's class.
lf l don't get in, l don't get my licence back.

26:11.353 --> 26:13.262
Sorry, Grant. Room 1 .

26:14.439 --> 26:15.518
Room 1 .

26:15.940 --> 26:18.017
Department of Motor Vehicles, please hold.

26:25.951 --> 26:29.035
-Hello, Jeff.
-Hi, Major. What are you doing here?

26:30.205 --> 26:31.748
Let's take a ride.

26:32.416 --> 26:33.591
Take a ride? Take a ride where?

26:37.695 --> 26:38.234
[ Skipped item nr. 257 ]

26:38.339 --> 26:39.963
Because l asked you to.

26:46.639 --> 26:48.912
-Did you read it?
-l'll show you my lD.

26:49.016 --> 26:51.999
lt gets me a beer in a disco in Encinitas.
What does yours get you?

26:52.104 --> 26:54.938
Mine gets me this.

26:57.442 --> 26:59.814
l could fix the licence, but not that picture.

27:03.240 --> 27:04.345
Am l under arrest?

27:04.450 --> 27:06.054
-What for? Did you do something wrong?
-No.

27:06.159 --> 27:07.348
-What's the matter?
-Nothing.

27:07.453 --> 27:10.122
Relax.
l just want to ask you a few questions.

27:14.710 --> 27:18.026
See that storefront over there? That's
Congressman Larkin's suburban office.

27:18.130 --> 27:21.333
Someone in there is selling nominations
to the service academies.

27:21.884 --> 27:23.657
lf someone's selling, someone's buying.

27:23.761 --> 27:25.220
Bingo. A-plus.

27:25.513 --> 27:27.339
ls that what you wanted to talk to me about?

27:30.476 --> 27:33.097
How long have you known Tony Stanton
and Tom Stubblefield?

27:33.354 --> 27:36.503
-All my life. They're my friends.
-Friends have a way of changing.

27:36.607 --> 27:38.814
-Now, wait a minute.
-How about their parents?

27:38.943 --> 27:40.341
Their parents are my friends, too.

27:40.445 --> 27:43.445
lf you think someone did something funny,
go talk to someone else.

27:44.991 --> 27:46.071
Okay.

27:53.292 --> 27:55.283
Which brings us to the Grants.

27:56.169 --> 27:59.254
-Your folks working late?
-Yeah, they're in the potting shed.

27:59.840 --> 28:03.174
-l guess the mushrooms are coming up.
-Can l go now?

28:03.594 --> 28:06.880
-Keep your ears open.
-You mean, sneak around my friends?

28:07.807 --> 28:09.955
You want to go to the Air Force Academy,
don't you?

28:10.059 --> 28:13.974
You think it's fair for a guy
to buy his way in? Take your place?

28:14.271 --> 28:16.181
No, no.

28:28.494 --> 28:30.903
And don't mention anything to your folks.

28:32.708 --> 28:35.495
-What do you mean?
-Let's keep this between us.

28:36.045 --> 28:37.243
Why?

28:38.088 --> 28:40.793
You wanted to surprise your parents,
didn't you?

28:41.050 --> 28:43.042
-Yeah.
-Okay.

28:46.180 --> 28:47.259
And Jeff...

28:49.225 --> 28:51.513
l'm glad you got your licence back.

29:00.903 --> 29:03.970
This one's pretty.
l think l'll take this one, too.

29:04.074 --> 29:06.564
No, if l take this one,
l'll have to have another one.

29:07.201 --> 29:09.278
That one. That one over there.

29:14.751 --> 29:17.242
-Jeff. Jeff, Jeff!
-What?

29:17.795 --> 29:18.942
Didn't l tell you fruit trees?

29:19.046 --> 29:20.737
Fruit trees? l thought this was a cactus sale.

29:20.841 --> 29:23.280
l want to dress it up a bit
with a pair of dwarf persimmons.

29:23.384 --> 29:26.090
Dwarf persimmons?
Fruit trees for short people.

29:26.513 --> 29:28.553
Bring out a Mexican Old Man.

29:29.308 --> 29:32.957
-Now l'm a social worker.
-You can take these right to the cashier.

29:33.062 --> 29:34.805
