56:58.726 --> 57:02.474
The smoked fish.
We traded our catch for the smoked fish.

57:06.860 --> 57:09.549
What do my parents have to do with all this?

57:09.653 --> 57:12.637
You remember l told you about sleepers,
the inactive agents?

57:12.741 --> 57:15.409
They were all sleepers.

57:15.743 --> 57:18.152
Your parents are the only two left.

57:20.374 --> 57:23.992
-Well, who's killing all these people? Us?
-No, of course not.

57:24.461 --> 57:28.874
-A renegade Soviet agent named Scuba.
-This is too much!

57:29.925 --> 57:32.214
What do you want from me?

57:33.137 --> 57:35.295
Stay around the house. Watch them.

57:35.556 --> 57:39.221
Look out for new faces.
Someone has got to contact them.

57:40.144 --> 57:42.101
Spy on my parents?

57:42.688 --> 57:44.515
You've gotta be kidding me.

57:44.648 --> 57:48.860
You want me to help you put them away.
Never!

57:51.114 --> 57:55.241
Look, Jeff, l know it's hard,
but you're going to have to face the facts.

57:55.994 --> 57:59.576
Look, Mr FBl Man,
if you're so sure and if you're so right...

57:59.830 --> 58:01.159
then why don't you arrest them?

58:04.336 --> 58:06.458
Because they haven't done anything yet.

58:07.172 --> 58:10.624
-You manipulating son of a bitch!
-Calm down!

58:11.300 --> 58:13.616
You don't have much choice.
They could be next.

58:13.720 --> 58:14.784
lt wouldn't break your heart.

58:14.888 --> 58:18.371
They're just bait for your Scuba guy, right?
All you care about is nailing him.

58:18.475 --> 58:20.551
You can come and identify the bodies.

58:50.091 --> 58:51.502
Good evening.

58:58.100 --> 59:01.931
We can't help you.
We haven't done anything for 20 years.

59:04.356 --> 59:06.313
l know what you haven't done.

59:06.734 --> 59:11.176
That is precisely
what makes you so valuable right now.

59:11.280 --> 59:13.772
Comrade Karpov, we are at your disposal.

59:14.700 --> 59:18.283
-But we're ill-equipped.
-Just follow the story.

59:19.247 --> 59:21.453
lt's all right there in front of you.

59:23.083 --> 59:27.792
A prick of a thorn and the princess sleeps.

59:28.923 --> 59:31.379
And many years later...

59:31.885 --> 59:34.920
the handsome prince awakens her.

59:35.262 --> 59:36.806
lt's all quite simple.

01:00:35.325 --> 01:00:37.781
lt's a true ensemble, the Kirov.

01:00:39.330 --> 01:00:43.790
l prefer it to the stars of the Bolshoi,
don't you agree, Elizabeth?

01:01:17.870 --> 01:01:19.068
We can't!

01:01:19.662 --> 01:01:22.035
Don't you see? We can't anymore.

01:01:22.791 --> 01:01:26.872
lt's been too long. We can't serve you now.
We're of no use.

01:01:27.546 --> 01:01:28.610
<i>We can't.</i>

01:01:28.714 --> 01:01:32.794
<i>-PIease understand, we can't.
-EIizabeth is understandabIy upset.</i>

01:01:32.968 --> 01:01:34.760
<i>But why be upset?</i>

01:01:35.638 --> 01:01:38.212
You're merely going to pay
a man some money.

01:01:44.730 --> 01:01:45.893
How much money?

01:01:51.904 --> 01:01:54.692
<i>-What kind of man?
-Scuba.</i>

01:01:54.950 --> 01:01:56.029
<i>Who?</i>

01:01:56.285 --> 01:01:59.119
<i>Your oId cIassmate from Gaczyna.</i>

01:01:59.370 --> 01:02:00.746
<i>Gaczyna.</i>

01:02:05.711 --> 01:02:07.502
English.

01:02:12.801 --> 01:02:13.964
<i>EngIish.</i>

01:02:19.558 --> 01:02:20.637
Please.

01:02:21.268 --> 01:02:23.261
l almost forgot.

01:02:24.105 --> 01:02:28.269
l brought you a little something.
From Beriozka.

01:02:29.819 --> 01:02:32.654
The good Beriozka on Gorky Street.

01:02:37.159 --> 01:02:38.489
How is....

01:02:38.704 --> 01:02:40.661
What is his name? Jeff?

01:02:43.749 --> 01:02:45.827
lt's a good likeness, don't you think?

01:03:54.865 --> 01:03:56.064
Don't shoot!

01:03:57.910 --> 01:03:59.404
Ms McLaughlin!

01:04:00.705 --> 01:04:02.533
ls this work experience?

01:04:04.834 --> 01:04:08.038
Go out in the yard. l'll be out in a minute.

01:04:14.261 --> 01:04:17.159
-Life's little surprises.
-No problem.

01:04:17.263 --> 01:04:19.636
l'll just go topless
for the rest of the student body.

01:04:24.271 --> 01:04:25.896
There you go, Judy.

01:04:32.947 --> 01:04:34.109
What are their names?

01:04:37.368 --> 01:04:38.431
lt's not important.

01:04:38.536 --> 01:04:41.027
What are their names?
What are my parents' names?

01:04:43.207 --> 01:04:48.358
Elizabeth Lazarova. Mikhail Stropovich.

01:04:48.462 --> 01:04:49.860
And what's my name?

01:04:49.964 --> 01:04:52.421
-Jeff.
-That's not a Russian name.

01:04:53.010 --> 01:04:54.406
You took a walk tonight, didn't you?

01:04:54.510 --> 01:04:57.346
You found something
you didn't want to find, right?

01:05:06.856 --> 01:05:09.064
Battle of Stalingrad.

01:05:11.237 --> 01:05:13.443
Probably belonged to one of their fathers.

01:05:14.698 --> 01:05:17.368
Pretty common. So many men went down.

01:05:17.785 --> 01:05:20.193
Hey, do l detect a little admiration there?

01:05:20.663 --> 01:05:22.537
For who, your parents? Yeah.

01:05:23.249 --> 01:05:24.363
Why?

01:05:25.543 --> 01:05:26.823
'Cause they had you.

01:05:27.670 --> 01:05:31.086
-Spare me the violins, G-man.
-No violins.

01:05:31.215 --> 01:05:32.446
Just a lot of hard work.

01:05:32.550 --> 01:05:35.123
You gotta be crazy
to bring a child into this ugly world.

01:05:35.261 --> 01:05:39.119
-What's so hard about it?
-Making a buck. Raising a family.

01:05:39.223 --> 01:05:42.973
Keeping it all together takes talent. Love.

01:05:47.733 --> 01:05:49.393
Put these back where you found them.

01:05:50.652 --> 01:05:52.062
Back to business, huh?

01:05:52.655 --> 01:05:54.149
G-man's onto something big.

01:05:55.074 --> 01:05:56.804
l'm trying to look out for you.

01:05:56.908 --> 01:05:59.182
Don't give me that crap!
You're out for yourself!

01:05:59.286 --> 01:06:03.018
The big collar. The major bust.
The two-bit G-man will shove it up your ass!

01:06:03.123 --> 01:06:04.187
Hey, hey, easy.

01:06:04.291 --> 01:06:05.702
You're not my father.

01:06:07.086 --> 01:06:08.829
You're not even my friend.

01:06:43.707 --> 01:06:46.280
-Now we have to tell him.
-No. No.

01:06:47.377 --> 01:06:48.540
lt would destroy him.

01:06:48.713 --> 01:06:51.286
You're wrong. He would understand.
l know he would.

01:06:51.590 --> 01:06:52.988
We must send him away.

01:06:53.092 --> 01:06:54.966
-Where?
-l don't know.

01:06:55.761 --> 01:06:58.494
We should call Bill,
have him put everything in Jeff's name.

01:06:58.599 --> 01:06:59.760
lt always was.

01:07:01.017 --> 01:07:03.686
-You knew this would happen?
-We both did.

01:07:05.771 --> 01:07:08.856
l'll never regret it. We had Jeff.

01:07:10.235 --> 01:07:11.610
l don't think it's over.

01:07:12.487 --> 01:07:14.444
Yes, it is.

01:07:15.240 --> 01:07:17.991
-lt can never be the same.
-We could run with Jeff.

01:07:18.201 --> 01:07:20.110
lt wouldn't be fair to him.

01:07:21.539 --> 01:07:23.615
He has his whole life ahead of him.

01:07:29.130 --> 01:07:30.291
We have to tell him.

01:07:33.926 --> 01:07:37.211
He probably wouldn't believe us.

01:07:38.973 --> 01:07:40.633
How could he?

01:07:59.703 --> 01:08:03.320
Hi, Mum. Hi, Dad. How was the ballet?

01:08:04.332 --> 01:08:06.409
-Very nice.
-Dad?

01:08:06.752 --> 01:08:08.210
Yeah. lt was very nice.

01:08:08.962 --> 01:08:11.632
Well, l think l'll turn in.

01:08:12.258 --> 01:08:15.839
-How's the new clutch?
-Great.

01:08:17.470 --> 01:08:20.636
Here, l almost forgot your change.

01:08:30.109 --> 01:08:31.568
What's my name?

01:08:33.779 --> 01:08:35.024
Come on, Dad.

01:08:35.490 --> 01:08:37.638
What could the head of the Grant family
have to hide...

01:08:37.742 --> 01:08:39.899
from his first and oldest and only son?

01:08:42.705 --> 01:08:44.200
What's my name?

01:08:47.126 --> 01:08:48.323
Nika.

01:08:52.924 --> 01:08:55.594
J. Nicholas Grant. Nick.

01:08:59.721 --> 01:09:00.969
Nikita.

01:09:08.691 --> 01:09:09.935
Hello.

01:09:10.318 --> 01:09:12.725
Your moment has come.

01:09:13.863 --> 01:09:15.854
<i>I toId you we're not ready.</i>

01:09:16.698 --> 01:09:19.107
You've had 20 years to get ready.

01:09:20.368 --> 01:09:22.243
-Who is it?
-lt's him.

01:09:22.371 --> 01:09:25.041
-Let's get out of here.
-lt's too late.

01:09:26.667 --> 01:09:29.504
-How about if you give us time?
-Hang up the phone.

01:09:29.712 --> 01:09:32.528
-How can we prevail?
-For God's sake, Dad!

01:09:32.631 --> 01:09:34.256
We beseech you!

01:09:35.135 --> 01:09:37.506
Your discipline is sorely wanting.

01:09:37.886 --> 01:09:39.928
The directorate will be most unhappy.

01:09:40.599 --> 01:09:43.054
You must go to work immediately.

01:09:43.184 --> 01:09:44.643
And if we don't?

01:09:45.770 --> 01:09:47.680
lf we choose not to?

01:09:48.481 --> 01:09:52.549
lf we have the strength to turn our back
on Elizabeth's father and my mother?

01:09:52.653 --> 01:09:53.982
Roy!

01:09:54.821 --> 01:09:55.901
Roy!

01:09:58.910 --> 01:09:59.989
Roy.

01:10:02.121 --> 01:10:03.200
Roy!

01:10:03.915 --> 01:10:06.870
You have neither the strength
nor the choice.

01:10:07.627 --> 01:10:09.335
<i>They are both dead.</i>

01:10:12.006 --> 01:10:14.213
<i>-Our parents are dead?
-Yes.</i>

01:10:16.844 --> 01:10:20.889
And to answer your next question,
of old age.

01:10:21.516 --> 01:10:24.304
-Roy!
-Now are you ready to proceed?

01:10:25.688 --> 01:10:27.229
-Roy!
-Give me your answer.

01:10:27.480 --> 01:10:28.711
<i>The answer is no.</i>

01:10:28.815 --> 01:10:32.813
Roy! Come on, where are you? lt's me, Jeff!

01:10:33.653 --> 01:10:36.324
Then we will have to skip a generation.

01:10:36.532 --> 01:10:37.611
Roy!

01:10:43.289 --> 01:10:45.364
Come in, Nikita. Sit down.

01:10:49.796 --> 01:10:51.539
Oh, my God!

01:10:51.923 --> 01:10:55.007
<i>No, not God. Just Nikita.</i>

01:10:56.094 --> 01:10:59.545
<i>You wiII make contact this morning at 5.:30.</i>

01:10:59.847 --> 01:11:02.803
<i>MeanwhiIe, Nikita and I
wiII keep each other company.</i>

01:11:02.935 --> 01:11:04.214
Please.

01:11:05.103 --> 01:11:07.676
Please, Konstantin lvanovich...

01:11:08.107 --> 01:11:11.309
l beg of you. Leave Jeff!

01:11:12.193 --> 01:11:15.563
<i>-Anything you say.
-You have heard what I said.</i>

01:11:15.740 --> 01:11:20.318
<i>5.:30 a.m., the G Street Pier.
You give him the money.</i>

01:11:22.121 --> 01:11:26.201
The boy is charming.
He looks just like his mother.

01:11:31.631 --> 01:11:33.670
You speak Russian, Nikita?

01:11:35.342 --> 01:11:38.012
No. And the name's Jeff.

01:11:38.596 --> 01:11:39.711
Jeff?

01:11:41.058 --> 01:11:43.974
To me, you are Nikita. And l am Konstantin.

01:11:44.811 --> 01:11:49.272
<i>You may call me tovarich.
lt's our Russian word for ''friend.''</i>

01:11:52.528 --> 01:11:54.816
Do you have another cigarette, Konstantin?

01:11:55.613 --> 01:12:00.027
You smoke, Nikita?
What would the Surgeon General say?

01:12:03.706 --> 01:12:05.284
Russian cigarettes.

01:12:06.833 --> 01:12:09.408
You will acquire the taste, Nikita.

01:12:10.379 --> 01:12:12.668
As you will for all things Russian.

01:12:15.551 --> 01:12:18.636
l once had some Popov Vodka.

01:12:19.180 --> 01:12:24.340
Did you? Bully for you, Nikita! What a guy!

01:12:27.563 --> 01:12:29.686
On your feet. We're leaving.

01:12:39.701 --> 01:12:42.240
-Where are you going?
-To the bathroom.

01:12:49.253 --> 01:12:52.289
You have a weak bladder, Nikita?

01:12:53.591 --> 01:12:54.966
Come again, Konstantin?

01:12:56.927 --> 01:12:58.006
Go.

01:12:58.638 --> 01:13:00.595
Make it snappy.

01:13:02.850 --> 01:13:04.558
Leave the door open.

01:13:15.531 --> 01:13:17.772
Stick this up your bladder, Boris.

01:13:30.003 --> 01:13:31.248
Let's go.

01:15:23.204 --> 01:15:25.327
-Karpov?
-He's got him!

01:15:25.540 --> 01:15:27.414
-You're next.
-You stay out of it!

01:15:27.958 --> 01:15:30.065
You're the bait. Karpov wants Scuba.

01:15:30.170 --> 01:15:31.961
We want Jeff.

01:15:33.006 --> 01:15:34.085
Alive!

01:15:35.133 --> 01:15:36.405
You've got to take me with you.

01:15:36.509 --> 01:15:38.032
-You need me!
-Step aside.

01:15:38.136 --> 01:15:40.011
The payoff is a trap!

01:15:40.472 --> 01:15:41.717
Here's the passports.

01:15:41.931 --> 01:15:43.704
He wants money. Karpov wants him.

01:15:43.808 --> 01:15:46.249
lf Scuba doesn't like the rendezvous,
you are next.

01:15:46.354 --> 01:15:48.709
-We'll take that chance.
-What do you think your odds are?

01:15:48.813 --> 01:15:51.254
He'll kill you! He'll kill anybody!

01:15:51.359 --> 01:15:53.381
-Okay?
-Okay, okay, what?

01:15:53.485 --> 01:15:56.885
-You tell me where the rendezvous is, okay?
-Okay, what?

01:15:56.989 --> 01:15:58.262
-What?
-You're not his father!

01:15:58.366 --> 01:16:00.554
Hey, hey, you got to trust me.

01:16:00.659 --> 01:16:03.780
Wait! Wait! Stop this damn truck!

01:16:35.071 --> 01:16:37.643
<i>-...is no.
-Roy!</i>

01:16:44.663 --> 01:16:47.534
<i>Come in, Nikita. Sit down.</i>

01:16:48.292 --> 01:16:50.035
<i>Oh, my God!</i>

01:16:50.335 --> 01:16:52.495
You are entering the United States illegally.

01:18:40.951 --> 01:18:43.109
Out! Out, out, out!

01:19:04.767 --> 01:19:07.803
No more of the monkey business! Drive!

01:20:56.299 --> 01:21:00.158
Come, come. Come, come. We go, we go.

01:21:00.263 --> 01:21:05.339
<i>WeIcome aboard the San Diego troIIey,
bound for San Ysidro InternationaI Border.</i>

01:21:07.102 --> 01:21:08.430
Go! Go, go, go!

01:21:23.203 --> 01:21:24.317
Up there.

01:21:46.643 --> 01:21:48.303
Where the hell is he?

01:22:00.907 --> 01:22:01.988
Richard!

01:22:04.578 --> 01:22:05.657
Jeff!

01:23:17.737 --> 01:23:19.510
-Richard, there it is! Over there!
-All right.

01:23:19.614 --> 01:23:21.690
-l see it! All right, all right!
-Faster! Faster!

01:23:50.021 --> 01:23:51.099
Richard!

01:23:57.612 --> 01:23:59.176
<i>Your attention, pIease.</i>

01:23:59.281 --> 01:24:04.348
<i>I'd Iike to remind aII passengers there is no
smoking, drinking, or eating permitted...</i>

01:24:04.453 --> 01:24:06.309
<i>whiIe onboard the troIIey.</i>

01:24:06.413 --> 01:24:08.870
<i>And in consideration to other passengers...</i>

01:24:09.083 --> 01:24:12.332
<i>pIease do not pIace your feet on the seats.
Thank you.</i>

01:24:59.385 --> 01:25:01.424
Take a seat, please. Please.

01:25:08.727 --> 01:25:12.511
We did our best. Don't take our son.

01:25:13.273 --> 01:25:15.314
lt wasn't good enough.

01:25:15.652 --> 01:25:17.312
Take us.

01:25:17.612 --> 01:25:20.697
But you are of no use to me
in Russia, Mikhail.

01:25:22.158 --> 01:25:25.526
<i>Our next station is Byer. Byer is next.</i>

01:25:30.667 --> 01:25:33.399
Anybody got any change?
Anybody got any change?

01:25:33.503 --> 01:25:35.651
Hey, how about you, lady? You got change?

01:25:35.756 --> 01:25:39.125
Anybody, change?
How about you guys, you got any change?

01:25:39.259 --> 01:25:41.783
Hey, how about you guys?
You look like buddies.

01:25:41.887 --> 01:25:44.010
Do you want to chip in together
to make change for me?

01:25:45.557 --> 01:25:47.846
<i>That's okay, hombre, l'll manage.</i>

01:25:48.353 --> 01:25:49.762
Don't move, folks.

01:25:50.187 --> 01:25:51.847
Everybody, steady.

01:26:00.031 --> 01:26:01.229
Konstantin.

01:26:01.783 --> 01:26:03.407
Roy, my friend.

01:26:04.285 --> 01:26:08.781
l lost you. 1967, Union Station.

01:26:11.877 --> 01:26:15.660
And now we have found each other.

01:26:16.214 --> 01:26:17.625
On the trolley.

01:26:19.509 --> 01:26:21.882
A chance encounter of old friends.

01:26:25.682 --> 01:26:30.095
You bring me my assignment.
What a friendly gesture.

01:26:32.189 --> 01:26:34.561
No? Did l presume too much?

01:26:36.235 --> 01:26:37.777
Of course, of course.

01:26:39.531 --> 01:26:40.858
l am mistaken.

01:26:42.616 --> 01:26:44.409
You hold all the cards.

01:26:46.246 --> 01:26:50.457
And all l have is a 1 7-year-old boy.

01:26:56.089 --> 01:26:57.548
Get up, Jeff.

01:27:01.553 --> 01:27:02.668
How?

01:27:03.013 --> 01:27:04.922
Like you always did, kid.

01:27:06.350 --> 01:27:08.805
What are you laughing at, scum?

01:27:16.109 --> 01:27:17.817
What did he say?

01:27:18.654 --> 01:27:22.070
''How can you let me go
after l killed your friend?''

01:27:22.241 --> 01:27:25.277
No, not friend, partner.

01:27:30.499 --> 01:27:33.251
-He tried to be--
-l heard what he said.

01:27:33.837 --> 01:27:37.750
''He tried to be a hero, he ended up a fool.''

01:27:50.520 --> 01:27:51.931
You heard me, kid.

01:27:53.273 --> 01:27:56.476
Plant your feet and rise. Now!

01:28:08.706 --> 01:28:11.078
On your feet, shithead! On your feet!

01:28:16.505 --> 01:28:19.792
All right, Jeff, cross the aisle...

01:28:21.343 --> 01:28:24.760
nice and slow.

01:28:33.439 --> 01:28:36.145
l would never give up a man
who killed my partner.

01:28:39.071 --> 01:28:41.822
You never had a partner.

01:28:49.623 --> 01:28:51.451
l like you, Roy.

01:29:00.259 --> 01:29:03.951
<i>Out Iast station
is San Ysidro InternationaI Border.</i>

01:29:04.055 --> 01:29:07.470
<i>AII returning passengers are reminded
to purchase new tickets....</i>

01:29:11.103 --> 01:29:13.891
You stay with me to the border.

01:30:29.560 --> 01:30:30.841
You stay here!

01:30:33.147 --> 01:30:34.544
You stay out of this!

01:30:34.648 --> 01:30:37.465
Come on. You walk in front of us, kid,
and hide this mess.

01:30:37.569 --> 01:30:39.608
-No! No!
-You don't want the cops here, do you?

01:30:44.618 --> 01:30:45.696
Jeffrey!

01:31:22.199 --> 01:31:24.190
Nikita, l'm going to miss you.

01:31:25.117 --> 01:31:29.863
We could have had such a pleasant trip
together. Come visit me sometime.

01:31:30.664 --> 01:31:33.453
And, by all means, bring Barbara with you.

01:31:52.187 --> 01:31:54.062
Goodbye, Mr Parmenter.

01:31:56.233 --> 01:31:58.107
Keep an eye out for me.

01:31:58.611 --> 01:32:00.769
l always have, Konstantin.

01:32:20.758 --> 01:32:22.087
You know, Roy...

